Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.08,0:22:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody's parents were multi-millionaire everybody lived on big estates everybody had\Nservants it was a so what yeah so what else is new you know it was just common all my friends
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.58,0:22:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,were millionaires it didn't mean anything at all um when one is spiritual um do they become more\Nintuitive the more spiritual you get or i think so yes i think they become more intuitive
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.40,0:22:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to\Nto
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.58,0:22:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to\Nthe non-verbal and the non-discrete the non-defined or are they just more in tune with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.30,0:23:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're more in tune with the field okay yeah they're more in tune with the field so if you're\Nspiritually aware you know somebody walks into the room you've already picked up a great deal of who
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.52,0:23:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,they are and where they're at without anything having been spoken i've already picked up their\Nenergy and you know whether they're up to good or no good or whether they're up to good or no good
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.25,0:23:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,good or no good or whether you have to lock the house when you're gone\Num what do they have um the 10 commandments um you know thou shall not kill um do not take up
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.39,0:23:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,false gods you know uh there's several different ones i can't think of yeah i know i know really\Nthere's 10 or is there 12 commandments there's 10 well the 10 that are in the bible
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.95,0:24:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but um what i'm saying is the 10 commandments um if you live your life but in your spiritual um\Nlife by the 10 commandments yes i isn't that good enough that i mean good enough for what
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.77,0:24:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be generally considered in the religious community as sufficient that you've lived by all\Ngod's commandments and you know someday you have to face god and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.27,0:24:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what can you say you can say i tried to live by all your commandments as i understood them oh lord\Nand if i was mistaken i asked for forgiveness and if you really screw up you got to go back
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.12,0:24:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and get reborn and redo the whole deal go back to sunday school learning right from wrong\Nwell let's see a lot of people don't value integrity or spiritual integrity it's not a value
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.12,0:25:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,if you watch television\Nyou'll see that you know other values are popularity or money or power over others political
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.53,0:25:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,power getting votes many things have served have um replaced uh spiritual values\Num is there a conflict from being spiritual and being in and making a good living is there a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.45,0:25:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you know is there any kind of conflict between the two\Nno
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.59,0:25:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is there any kind of conflict between the two\Nyeah it's a big and a lot of times it's assumed by naive people that to be spiritual you really
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.49,0:25:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,should be poor well and that the rich people have no chance of getting into heaven what is it this\Nthing a rich person has the biggest chance of getting into heaven as a what is it something the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.73,0:25:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,eye of a needle yeah yeah some do the eye of a needle yeah they don't mean literally so they\Nmean that the ego of such a person generally
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.72,0:26:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,point, that doesn't mean it's impossible, but generally, probably, nine out of ten,\Nwho have become so worldly as to become, you know, super rich and super famous, that their
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.02,0:26:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,value, their values would preclude, preclude their spiritual advancement.\NWell, we all know that certain spiritual teachers fall into certain, there's certain categories
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.40,0:26:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,such as, you know, worship, you know, they want to be worshipped, you know, they want\Nwealth, they, there's certain...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.90,0:26:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, they're professional gurus, yeah.\NThere's certain downfalls of these gurus that will take you down a wrong path.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.94,0:26:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego and money.\NRight, and, you know, I'm sure that there's chinks in the armor that everybody's looking
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.48,0:26:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for, you know.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.07,0:26:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always going to be something that someone can say.\NThere's always going to be something that someone can say about any spiritual life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.47,0:27:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They do about us.\NThey do?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.13,0:27:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's all kinds of...\NYeah, show me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.36,0:27:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's all kinds of people out there that doubt, so...\NDoubt, oh, doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.08,0:27:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and...\NWell, they doubt spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.84,0:27:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it that you and I, they doubt spiritual reality, or diminish its value, devalue it,\Nbut that's a personal option on their part, and of course, whether you value it or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.16,0:27:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it's important to know that that will likely change over time.\NThere was a time in my life when I was extremely religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.81,0:27:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there was a time in my life when I became a devout atheist.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.71,0:27:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was devoutly atheistic as I once was devoutly religious.\NIn both cases, I was worshiping truth, because I thought atheism was truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.80,0:28:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to me, truth became the high priority, not the divinity of our creator.\NAnd I grew up with some other adolescents who all scoffed at religion, all scoffed at religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.34,0:28:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all atheists, and I was very religious.\NSo, they would give me a hard time all the time, all the time about it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.74,0:28:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I learned that...\NIt was to keep one's religious, personal religious views to one's self,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.36,0:28:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe share them only with others who have an equal viewpoint.\NSo, in other words, it's best not to say too much until you figure out what the climate is.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.36,0:28:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's correct.\NSo, my religiosity would maybe look like a fool to my atheistic friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.80,0:29:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who are just into intellectualism.\NAnd it was funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.54,0:29:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's many paradoxes, you know.\NDo human beings have a personal will, or are we only witnessing the divine will?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.06,0:29:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have a personal will, and that's part of divine will.\NPart of divine will is that each one of us has the freedom of a personal will,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.54,0:29:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,by which our own will is free.\NBy which our own will is free.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.38,0:29:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,By which our own will is free.\NBy which our own will is free.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.50,0:29:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,By which our own karma is decided, that we are all given freedom of choice.\NSo, we are all given sort of a great latitude to become that which we intend for ourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.50,0:30:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,some of which we can be responsible for, some we can't.\NSome we were conditioned before we had a choice, before we remember a choice in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.39,0:30:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But some...\NSome of us, you know, are really living out choices made in prior lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.54,0:30:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You teach that beauty is a shortcut to God.\NThat what is?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.02,0:30:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Beauty is a shortcut to God.\NFrom, you know, from music to opera to...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.80,0:30:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All beauty, all aesthetic.\NAnd it shows appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.03,0:30:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say beauty is an expression of divinity in a different dimension, you know, than the intellectual.\NAnd then at a certain point of life, you see the beauty of everything that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.61,0:31:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the beauty of all that exists.\NEverything that exists is divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.22,0:31:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say that divinity is the requirement for existence.\NAnd then from an absolutist viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.65,0:31:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing exists except divinity.\NThe capacity to exist is already an expression of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.56,0:31:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality, nothing exists except divinity.\NDisguised as an old shoe or a beautiful lily, but still the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.90,0:31:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Aesthetically, we might say one is different than the other,\Nbut existentially, they're both the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.78,0:31:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,An old shoe or a lily share the fact that divinity exists.\NSomeone has asked you to say something about A.A. and Bill Wilson,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.62,0:32:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,since you have a vantage point, you know, of producing his...\Nwhat he believed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.30,0:32:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, we've discussed Bill Wilson many times.\NHave we?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.46,0:32:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.46,0:32:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, would you say that...\NI mean, he had...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.30,0:32:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw through him...\Nvery...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.30,0:32:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,very similar experiences of people who...\NI mean, we have people that have seen you one time and have gotten sober.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.30,0:32:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.\NDue to the energy, and so, I mean, we have several people that have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.80,0:32:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo, would you say that if they were to go to find some religious person or place, that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.14,0:32:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that would...\Nthat would help these people that do have a problem with addiction?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.48,0:32:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, addiction is just one of many problems.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.48,0:32:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Consulting a person...\Npeople of advanced spiritual development can be of assistance to anything, including
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.96,0:32:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,addictions.\NSometimes, merely one visit with a very powerful spiritual teacher is all that's required,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.96,0:33:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're right on the verge of it, and that addition of the energy of the teacher\Nis all that's required.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.18,0:33:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I mean, that's...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.18,0:33:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.88,0:33:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.88,0:33:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.88,0:33:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.22,0:33:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.22,0:33:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.22,0:33:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.29,0:33:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.29,0:33:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.29,0:33:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd then, that mate, the person or the teacher transmits, transmits automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.96,0:33:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to the listener.\NThe value of hearing of an advanced teacher is that you automatically pick up the energies,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.23,0:33:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and they become now available to you.\NSo, once you've been in the presence of a great teacher, that teachers' level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.78,0:33:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is not available to you as an option.\NIt's an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.12,0:34:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,not a necessity, nor would a great teacher want it to be anything other\Nthan an option. To see the beauty of all that exists is obvious to a person who
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.46,0:34:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,sees the beauty of all exists. It is not so obvious to a person who sees a dead\Nrabbit on the road. I agree with him. So when you say that beauty is a shortcut
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.58,0:34:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to God, you're saying that if you can embrace that beauty and understand it\Nand take it upon you, that you'll feel the presence of God in that particular
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.15,0:34:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,moment. One doesn't define it mentally that way. You know, you can be in a state\Nof beatitude and the word God never goes through your mind. Or one
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.67,0:35:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,can be constantly\Naware of the presence of God and not go into what the world calls an advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.19,0:35:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,state. My present state, for instance, I'm aware of the presence of God constantly.\NIt's a constant presence without verbalizing it mentally. All that I do,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.08,0:35:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,all that I am, all the decisions that I make, everywhere I may go, whatever I may\Ndo, is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.66,0:35:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,resolved then in the presence of God. In the back of my mind, I talk to God all the\Ntime.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.02,0:35:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So can you go about your daily tasks and still, you know, be spiritual because you\Nhave God? It's sort of like a split personality. You're doing the dishes and you're doing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.04,0:35:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the vacuuming and you're doing the dustings, but in the back of your mind, God's always\Npresent.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.88,0:35:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not split. It's more that the awareness of the presence of God envelops\Neverything inclusively.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.63,0:36:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ok.\NWithin the inclusiveness, are the daily duties of washing the floor, and running
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.25,0:36:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a vacuum cleaner, and talking to friends on the phone.\NOk.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.57,0:36:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also the awareness suddenly that goes on at all times, that one is answerable\Nto God for one's state of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.29,0:36:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ok.\Nallow yourself to be disrupted and angry, etc. If it happens, you apologize to God and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.30,0:37:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, I pray for forgiveness for my humanness and for the predominance of emotionality.\NSo we can't be in a beatific state at all times and in all places under all circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.28,0:37:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,unless one is in an extremely advanced level in which nothing that happens matters to you\Nall that much one way or the other, because it lacks an intrinsic reality. It's a phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.28,0:37:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but not all phenomena are really a reality. On the other hand, in another level of consciousness,\Nall phenomena are the expression of reality. Our sitting here and talking to each other this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.66,0:37:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is a phenomena that occurs within the province of divinity, the versatility of divinity to express\Nitself in multiple ways. One way is you and I sitting here talking about divinity. You and I
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.31,0:37:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,sitting here talking about divinity. You and I sitting here talking about divinity.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.45,0:37:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.67,0:37:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.19,0:38:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How many Americans are sitting at breakfast time this morning talking about divinity?\NWhat percentage?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.35,0:38:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NI don't know. Let's ask. Can we ask the arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.58,0:38:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NCome on. We can ask the arm. People talking about divinity at breakfast time is more than 10%,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.80,0:38:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 5%, 6%. Maybe 5% of people do talk about divinity.\NBut that's just like you said that, you know, you can't talk about divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.15,0:38:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can walk down the street and you ask how many people what their goal is and maybe one in a million or more would say my goal is enlightenment.\NTo become enlightened would be rare, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.33,0:38:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, very uncommon to have that.\NWell, it's supposedly, for one thing, too difficult. The ego is so pervasive and dominant and tenacious that the average person has little chance of achieving its goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.34,0:38:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.90,0:38:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.46,0:38:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.60,0:38:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.74,0:38:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.92,0:38:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.06,0:38:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.18,0:38:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.34,0:38:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.48,0:38:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.62,0:39:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\Nchance of transcending it unless they go off to a seminary and very special circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.73,0:39:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,disconnect the phone, don't go to the mailbox, don't deal with money, and don't deal with\Nthe banks, forget the stock market, forget the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.08,0:39:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I say you can do both.\NYou can live in the world and simultaneously be extremely spiritually dedicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.56,0:39:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think everyone sets it up like, they set it up that if they are a very wealthy\Nperson, they're not spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.63,0:39:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's an artificial separation.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.47,0:39:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But they, a lot of people believe that, that if there's a, if they're a wealthy person,\Nthey're not spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.53,0:39:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I think that a lot of people look-\NWell, it's like saying that if they're poor, they more likely would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.87,0:40:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo, a lot of people look at it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.87,0:40:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people look then if, you know, you know and I know that you have to be firm with\Npeople sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.82,0:40:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you're firm with them, then they say, oh, they're just that way because they\Nthink they can boss anybody around.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.67,0:40:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's like the defensive, I've heard it over and over again, people, not about\Nme, but other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.33,0:40:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI've said that about other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.33,0:40:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm just saying that, you know, there is a, in the spiritual community, there seems\Nto be some kind of, you know, if you are well fixed, you can't be spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.50,0:40:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThere are, there are, many people believe that way, that if you're rich, you can't really
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.02,0:41:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,be religious or truly spiritual, and vice versa, that if you were truly spiritual and\Ntruly religious, you wouldn't be poor, because you get off your lazy butt and go and get a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.79,0:41:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,job.\NYeah, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.03,0:41:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a, you know, it's, it's just, you know, it's an oxymoron, you know, it's like.\NOxymoron, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.22,0:41:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.22,0:41:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be truthful without becoming, without coming across as unkind?\NI think it's a matter of a delicacy of expression, consideration for the feelings of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.61,0:41:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Consideration for other people's feelings.\NThat's the whole idea, really, behind politeness, is to be considerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.73,0:41:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the person doesn't notice they drop something on the rug, and you say to them,\Noh, you dropped so-and-so on the rug.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.98,0:42:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The person wasn't aware of that at the time, so you try to express it in a way that's non-moralistic\Nor condemnatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.75,0:42:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.00,0:42:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we can be responsible for things that are, that, that have no morality associated\Nwith them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.42,0:42:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NYou know, you can accidentally step on the dog's paw.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.48,0:42:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't mean to do that.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.93,0:42:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean you're bad.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.62,0:42:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the difference between being spiritual and being religious?\NSpiritual is more abstract and of a higher dimension than religiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.06,0:42:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSpiritual is of a higher definition.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.08,0:43:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Religiosity has a very specific meaning.\NSpirituality means the value of things that are non-physical and non-necessarily logical
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.63,0:43:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or within the realm of reason, things of a greater value, of a greater dimension.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.42,0:43:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou know, the value of human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.03,0:43:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's say that-\NThat's why I don't believe in capital punishment, because there's no way you can excuse it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.73,0:43:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can rationalize it and hope that it will tend to diminish crime.\NI don't think it does, but there's no way you can make it abstract.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.69,0:43:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very concrete, discreet act.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.35,0:43:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NSo as far as it goes, as our spiritual being, we would say that to increase one's spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.41,0:44:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,... to increase one's own spiritual beliefs, we would have to be also religious and ...\NNo, you don't have to be religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.56,0:44:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NBut if you are spiritual, you see the value of our religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.13,0:44:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NBecause you see that the essence of that religion is really its spirituality ...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.13,0:44:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\N... to a higher dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.79,0:44:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you do something, even though it's sort of stupid in a way, but you do it because\Nyour religion requires it, you're doing it out of your reverence for God and the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.84,0:44:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that, you know, it is of service to mankind to be more spiritually inclined and less physical.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.40,0:44:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Less moralistic.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.12,0:45:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you could say how all of us could become more spiritual, what would you give us as\Nadvice?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.09,0:45:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I could tell people, first of all, read what is generally called the world's great\Nspiritual literature, the great classics that have withstood the ... that have gone on for
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.00,0:45:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,centuries, the great spiritual classics of all time, because you'll get something out\Nof reading every single one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.55,0:45:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIt's impossible to read the great spiritual classics of all time without being affected
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.88,0:45:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,by what one has just read.\NEveryone gets totally affected by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.16,0:45:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Become acquainted with the great spiritual classics.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.38,0:45:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that will take you some ... on the path towards becoming more spiritual?\NWell, the great spiritual classics will define for you things that you had not defined before.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.34,0:46:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.34,0:46:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Point out things that you did not realize the importance of.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.34,0:46:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what would you classify as the great spiritual classics?\NThe great ... don't ask me that, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.34,0:46:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.34,0:46:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have to think about it.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.34,0:46:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, now you want me to go into the realm of thinking.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.95,0:46:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NThe great spiritual classics, the Bhagavad Gita.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.32,0:46:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NThe Holy Bible, the New Testament.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.51,0:46:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThe Course of Common.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.51,0:46:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.51,0:46:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.51,0:46:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.51,0:46:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.51,0:46:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.51,0:46:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.51,0:46:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.92,0:46:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.56,0:46:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just curious because actually all of us want to become more spiritual.\NNot necessarily more religious but more spiritual — — — because that seems to be the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.75,0:46:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThat's a goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.75,0:47:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a goal.\NSo, you know, all of our followers would like to, you know, become more spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.89,0:47:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo we can do that through service.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.27,0:47:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do that through donations.\NWe can do that through reading, actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.62,0:47:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything speaks of helpfulness to others, kindness, consideration.\NEvery act of kindness is a prayer to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.36,0:47:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If I would step on a doggie's paw by accident, which I did,\Non the edge of her paw, I apologized to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.53,0:47:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though she doesn't understand half the time, you apologized.\NShe understands love.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.18,0:47:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get me wrong.\NThe dog understands love.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.41,0:47:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I step on her paw by accident, and I say,\NKelsey, oh, honey, I'm sorry, I put my arms around her,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.08,0:48:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the doggie understands that.\NLet's ask her out on this side of the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.64,0:48:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The doggie understands that.\NYep, the doggie understands that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.22,0:48:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That that was a mistake.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.76,0:48:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NSo if we were to do that, say, to our enemies, the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.21,0:48:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry that happened.\NWell, we all regretted World War II, that what was necessary was necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.48,0:48:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I was a minesweeper.\NAnd so you regretted any damage to anybody or any person.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.32,0:48:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to do it because the war was on,\Nand you didn't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.53,0:48:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you refused an order, you'd be court-martialed.\NSo we had to do things that were, that I'm glad,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.36,0:49:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,there were many things that many of them had to do,\Nwhich I was not required to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.06,0:49:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very grateful to God.\NI said, dear God, I give thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.96,0:49:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My life was devoted to keeping the crew alive\Nand getting us through typhoons
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.47,0:49:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and keeping us from being capsized and stuff.\NAnd I thanked many God.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.42,0:49:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I thanked God then as I thank him now.\NBut I was not called upon to kill someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.81,0:49:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So I cannot say what my decision would have been.\NYou see that man over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.08,0:49:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to shoot him.\NYou know, where would my allegiance have been
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.66,0:49:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to God which forbid the killing of anybody under anything?\NOnly under certain circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.11,0:49:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that apply?\NDoes it always apply?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.21,0:49:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it never apply?\NSo I was always grateful that I never had to make that decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.80,0:50:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I was never commanded to kill anyone.\NI was commanded to keep us alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.79,0:50:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no problem with that.\NKeep us going through the great typhoons and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.22,0:50:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So my life was devoted to saving life and not taking it.\NSo I just consider that a gift that God gave me,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.57,0:50:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that I never had to pull the trigger\Nbecause I don't know what I would have done
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.65,0:50:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if I sighted another human being within the gun sights.\NWell, if he was classified as evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.15,0:50:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I would have had to pull the trigger\Nbecause he was evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.53,0:50:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wasn't killing anything except evil.\NEven the world had that trouble with Adolf Hitler.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.88,0:50:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't know what to do with him.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.34,0:50:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NSo when we say...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.14,0:51:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What is meant by spiritual?\NIt is a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.10,0:51:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Way of viewing the world.\NOverall, contextualizing the world
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.24,0:51:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and its significance and meaning\Nand the implications for your own individual life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.41,0:51:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I consider our talking to each other right now\Nto be a great privilege.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.82,0:51:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thank God for it.\NThank you, dear Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.92,0:51:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have been...\Nallowed to have this discourse
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.26,0:51:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in the presence of the public\Nand to do so with the help of my wife, Susan,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.38,0:51:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,who is very loving and helpful\Nwith all of our spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.02,0:51:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of its expressions,\Nas well as our other friends, close friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.84,0:51:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who played such an important part in our lives,\Nfor whom I am very grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.14,0:51:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, honey.\NThank you, honey, for thanking me, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.72,0:52:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou're a great wife, Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.98,0:52:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And I love you to pieces.\NYou're adorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.52,0:52:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, is that about good enough?\NWas that about an hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.92,0:52:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was.\NOh, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.62,0:52:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!\NYay!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.56,0:52:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it?\NWhen we do these 10 Ghosts so fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.96,0:52:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I think 20 minutes has gone by.
